{"id":"2304.12260","submitter":"Barnab\\'as Janzer","authors":"Barnab\\'as Janzer and Oliver Janzer","title":"On locally rainbow colourings","comments":"12 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Given a graph $H$, let $g(n,H)$ denote the smallest $k$ for which the\nfollowing holds. We can assign a $k$-colouring $f_v$ of the edge set of $K_n$\nto each vertex $v$ in $K_n$ with the property that for any copy $T$ of $H$ in\n$K_n$, there is some $u\\in V(T)$ such that every edge in $T$ has a different\ncolour in $f_u$.\n  The study of this function was initiated by Alon and Ben-Eliezer. They\ncharacterized the family of graphs $H$ for which $g(n,H)$ is bounded and asked\nwhether it is true that for every other graph $g(n,H)$ is polynomial. We show\nthat this is not the case and characterize the family of connected graphs $H$\nfor which $g(n,H)$ grows polynomially. Answering another question of theirs, we\nalso prove that for every $\\varepsilon>0$, there is some $r=r(\\varepsilon)$\nsuch that $g(n,K_r)\\geq n^{1-\\varepsilon}$ for all sufficiently large $n$.\n  Finally, we show that the above problem is connected to the\nErd\\H{o}s-Gy\\'arf\\'as function in Ramsey Theory, and prove a family of special\ncases of a conjecture of Conlon, Fox, Lee and Sudakov by showing that for each\nfixed $r$ the complete $r$-uniform hypergraph $K_n^{(r)}$ can be edge-coloured\nusing a subpolynomial number of colours in such a way that at least $r$ colours\nappear among any $r+1$ vertices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Apr 2023 17:00:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-25"}
